<subSubSection id="D9F16554FFBABA16B3E2FF58BBF1F5C5" pageId="6" pageNumber="625" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="915436DFFFBABA16B3E2FF58BBF1F5C5" blockId="6.[2029,2625,2025,2452]" lastBlockId="6.[1411,2626,2458,3478]" pageId="6" pageNumber="625">
<taxonomicName id="56EB4D5CFFBABA16B3E2FF58BAEBF79E" authorityName="Johnson" authorityYear="1952" box="[2032,2253,2104,2128]" class="Mammalia" family="Molossidae" genus="Molossus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="625" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="milleri">Molossus ntilleri</taxonomicName>
was ﬁrst described as M. fuliginmus, which was previously used to describe another taxon. Therefore, the name 
<taxonomicName id="56EB4D5CFFBABA16BC59FFCFBAEBF708" authorityName="Johnson" authorityYear="1952" box="[2123,2253,2222,2246]" class="Mammalia" family="Molossidae" genus="Molossus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="625" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="milleri">M. millm&quot;</taxonomicName>
was proposed as a substitute, wholly synonymous with M. ﬁdlgino. sus based on same type specimen and locality. Molecular studies demonstrated that mastiﬂ' bats from eastern 
<collectingCountry id="E9FC764FFFBABA16BD5FFE2CBBB1F6AB" box="[2381,2455,2380,2405]" name="Cuba" pageId="6" pageNumber="625">Cuba</collectingCountry>
, Cayman lslands, andjaınaica are genetically the same species; however, M. hopidorhyrtchus from the type locality of 
<collectingRegion id="532FF83DFFBABA16BCF7FEFCBB68F67A" box="[2277,2382,2460,2484]" country="Cuba" name="La Habana" pageId="6" pageNumber="625">Havana</collectingRegion>
in western 
<collectingCountry id="E9FC764FFFBABA16BDE7FEFBB819F67A" box="[2549,2623,2459,2484]" name="Cuba" pageId="6" pageNumber="625">Cuba</collectingCountry>
has been reported as smaller in body size. Therefore, there is still a question ifthere are two allopatric species of 
<taxonomicName id="56EB4D5CFFBABA16B2CCFE8AB577F5CC" authorityName="E. Geoffroy" authorityYear="1805" box="[1758,1873,2538,2562]" class="Mammalia" family="Molossidae" genus="Molossus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="625" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Molossus</taxonomicName>
in 
<collectingCountry id="E9FC764FFFBABA16B369FE8AB5E3F5CC" box="[1915,1989,2538,2562]" name="Cuba" pageId="6" pageNumber="625">Cuba</collectingCountry>
that needs to be resolved. Monotypic.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
